subject: p15338518
Findings: Endotracheal tube terminates approximately 56 cm above the carina and is adequately placed. Right internal jugular line ends at mid Svc. A feeding tube is seen to course below the diaphragm into the stomach however, the distal end is beyond the radiographic view. Left lower lung opacities reflecting combination of atelectasis and mild pleural effusion is unchanged since. Mildly enlarged heart and mediastinal contours are stable.
